This paper focuses on the problem of identifying subsets of validation data where machine learning models perform poorly, which is a common problem in model validation. This problem is closely related to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as data management (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as fraud detection, which could fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.DB, cs.CR, and cs.CY.
